go-to: zhili_congress_menu

= Party Congress

{!<svg id="reichstag" style="width: 500px; height: 250px;"> </svg>!}

With the news coming in and the Brockdorff cabinet still busy discussing course of action, the SPD has called a party conference in the town of [BLANK]. As the delegates make their way in from all over the country, the atmosphere is weirdly tense, in part due to how unusual it is. 

The SPD has not traditionally taken strong action on foreign affairs. However, Stresemann's proposal to intervene in 1924 led to outrage from the war weary German population, causing his and Reichskanzler Arthur von Posadowsky-Wehner's entire cabinet to fall. Meanwhile . Many in our party left, previously aligned with the USPD, have . .

Even so, the conference was met with significant doubt from many of the delegates who are more distrustful of the party leadership across the entire SPD aisle, and thus come with a degree of opposition to any decisions that can be made here.

At , Party Chairman Hermann Muller , 

