@zhili_congress_menu

- @antiwar: German Imperialism is a cruel blight on our nation. We must harshly oppose further intervention.
- @prowar: Japan is the real threat to the people of Asia. We must try to convince the party to support the conflict to stop another Imperialist regime. 
- @neutral: Too many lives are at stake here. The SPD should take a neutral stance on the matter for now. Party members should avoid talking about the war to their constituents whilst we watch and see.
- @principled: We must offer principled opposition against both sides. Japan and Germany are equally as guilty in their actions. 
- @free: We must avoid taking an unified stance on the matter, we shall issue an internal declaration to push for the representatives freedom of choice on the matter.
- @china: What should matter the most is China, not Japan or Germany. The Zhili are corrupt and ineffective, therefore the SPD must consider support for a Chinese Faction and push German politics towards their favour. 
- @ignore: Rather than focusing on social matters, the SPD should actively ignore the war and focus on issues that affect the workers here and now.

@antiwar 
subtitle: This option lets us capitalize on German weariness to the conflicts and wars we've been getting into, however we will have to convince the dissenting factions.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_antiwar = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 

@prowar 
subtitle: This option is highly unpopular around the party, we will have a tough time convincing them. 
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_prowar = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@neutral
subtitle: There are some demands for action, we'll have to address them.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_neutral = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@principled
subtitle: A prime compromise between many differing viewpoints, this is not hard to convince the congress, however some of the more extreme hawks or doves will be disappointed. 
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_principled = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@free
subtitle: Not hard to get it passed, but after calling the congress, representatives are expecting to come out with a decision.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_free = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@china
subtitle: This option is seen by many as insane, it is going to lead to a lot of discussion around the party, but we might be able to choose a warlord to support?...
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_china = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@ignore
subtitle: Focus on bread and gas prices.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_ignore = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 

@negotiations 
on-arrival: {!

Q.total_vote_pool = ((Q.reformist_influence) + (Q.labor_influence) + (Q.left_influence) + (Q.center_influence));

Q.total_vote_pool_support = (Q.total_vote_pool);

Q.zhilivotesupport = (Q.total_vote_pool_support).toFixed(1);

!}
go-to: zhili-negotiation-menu

hi we're negotiating testt

our support is [+ zhilivotesupport +]

@zhili-negotiation-menu

- @vote: Let's bring it to a vote.
- @noopposition: The party has agree
- @favours: Do we have any leverage we can use to tilt the vote?

@vote
choose-if: zhilivotesupport >= 50

